HEADWORD: Euthiochroic
<hw>Eu`thi*o*chro"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ sulphur + <?/ color.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or denoting, an acid so
called.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Euthiochroic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
complex derivative of hydroquinone and sulphonic (thionic) acid. -- so
called because it contains sulphur, and forms brilliantly colored
(yellow) salts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euthyneura</ent>⟦br⟧
